ing the difficulties involved, they identify the types of social policies that can blunt or counter these negative effects. They also suggest that international governance will have a growing influence on how globalization affects individual nations. The up-to-date, empirically rich case studies in the book cover the experiences of Brazil, Mexico, the Philippines, South Africa, South Korea, Spain, and Turkey.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh1 aBizberg, Ilán, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBland, Gary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBland, Gary, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFriedman, Steven, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeyman, E. Fuat, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaquian, Aprodicio A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoon, Chung-in, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchwartzman, Simon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTulchin, Joseph S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTulchin, Joseph S., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aYang, Jae-jin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertLynne Rienner Press Complete eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311078425140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978168585130940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781685851309423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781685851309/original  a978-3-11-078425-1  Lynne Rienner Press Complete eBook-Package 2013-2000c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EB